@startuml 05-video-deletion

!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
title Flow 5: Video Deletion (Developer Initiated)

actor "Developer" as Dev
participant "Platform\nBackend" as Backend
participant "Platform\nSmart Contract" as Contract
database "Sui\nBlockchain" as Sui
database "Walrus\nStorage" as Walrus
database "Cache\nLayer" as Cache

== Delete Request ==

Dev -> Backend: DELETE /videos/{video_id}\nAuthorization: Bearer {api_key}

Backend -> Backend: Validate API key\nResolve to dev_account

Backend -> Contract: get_video(video_id)
Contract -> Sui: Read Video object
Sui --> Contract: Video {owner, blob_ids, sui_obj_ids, ...}
Contract --> Backend: video

alt Developer is not owner
    Backend --> Dev: 403 Forbidden
else Developer is owner

    == Delete Blobs from Walrus ==

    loop For each blob in video
        Backend -> Walrus: walrus delete\n--object-id {sui_obj_id}
        Walrus -> Walrus: Mark blob as deleted
        Walrus --> Backend: Storage resource reclaimed
    end

    note right of Walrus
      Storage resource is freed
      and can be REUSED for
      new blob uploads.
    end note

    == Burn Sui Objects & Update State ==

    Backend -> Contract: delete_video(video_id)

    loop For each blob Sui object
        Contract -> Sui: Burn blob object
        Sui --> Contract: Storage rebate (SUI)
    end

    Contract -> Sui: Delete Video object
    Contract -> Sui: Credit storage rebate\nto DeveloperAccount
    Sui --> Contract: Success
    Contract --> Backend: Deleted\n+ rebate amount

    == Invalidate Cache ==

    Backend -> Cache: Invalidate all keys\nfor video_id
    Cache --> Backend: Purged

    Backend --> Dev: 200 OK\n{\n  deleted: true,\n  storage_resource_freed: "X bytes",\n  sui_rebate: "Y SUI"\n}

    note right of Contract
      Developer receives:
      1. Storage resource back (reusable for new uploads)
      2. SUI storage rebate (from burning Sui objects)
    end note
end

@enduml
